alert.note: Alert for King (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued November 04 at 10:24AM PDT until November 05 at 9:46AM PDT by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The National Weather Service in Seattle WA has issued a Flood Warning for the following rivers in Washington... Tolt River Above Carnation affecting King County. .An atmospheric river will continue to bring heavy rainfall to the area today. This is expected to bring the Tolt River at Carnation above flood stage. ...FLOOD WARNING IN EFFECT UNTIL LATE TOMORROW MORNING... * WHAT...Moderate flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Tolt River Above Carnation. * WHEN...Until late tomorrow morning. * IMPACTS...At 5,000.0 cfs, the Tolt River will flood Tolt River Rd NE and many driveways. Some homes in the San Souci area could be inaccessible due to deep and quick flood waters. This river level on the Tolt corresponds to a phase 3 flood in the King County flood system. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 9:15 AM PDT Friday the flow was 2,510.0 cfs. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage this afternoon to a crest of 7,144.5 cfs late this afternoon. It will then fall below flood stage just after midnight tonight. - Flood flow is 5,000.0 cfs. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Stay tuned to further developments by listening to your local radio, television, or NOAA Weather Radio for further information. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by this evening at 630 PM PDT.
